Blue - chip stocks hammered by inflation worries . The Dow Jones industrial average fell nearly 150 points Friday on signs that underlying inflation was showing some unwanted vitality and as long - term interest rates soared to the highest levels since last July . Based on early and unofficial data , the Dow finished with a loss of 148 . 36 points , or 2 . 27 percent , at 6 , 391 . 69 . It was off 134 . 38 points for the week , its fifth straight down week . The last time the index racked up such a string of declining weeks was in the last quarter of 1991 . In the broader market , declining issues swamped advances 23 - 3 on active volume of 442 million shares on the New York Stock Exchange . 
